1. To show your custom application in Gnome 3 launcher, add "APP_NAME.desktop" inside "/usr/share/applications".
Example for adding Spring Tool Suite to Gnome 3 launcher.

File name: spring.desktop

[Desktop Entry]
Name=Spring IDE
Comment=Develop Spring Applications
Icon=spring-icon
Exec=/media/padmahasa/personal/sts-4.14.1.RELEASE/SpringToolSuite4
Terminal=false
Type=Application
Categories=Utility
StartupNotify=true
Name[en_US]=Spring IDE


2. Add ".svg" formatted icon into below paths.
/usr/share/icons/hicolor/scalable/apps/spring-icon.svg
/usr/share/icons/spring-icon.svg
